folder: Flatbush Avenue & Snyder Avenue, Brooklyn, NY
text:
Flatbush Ave., at the N.E. corner of Snyder Ave., showing the Grace Dutch Reformed Church Erected in 1871, razed in 1924.

May 1923.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

*Incorrect. This is the Chapel of the Reformed Dutch Church of Flatbush.

folder: Flatbush Avenue & Snyder Avenue, Brooklyn, NY
text:
(1)
Flatbush Ave., east side, north from, but not including Snyder Ave., showing the Dutch Reformed Church of Flatbush, at the S.W. corner of Church Ave. The buildings are draped with flags as part of the "Flatbush land boom celebration".
October 1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(2)
The same, showing the corner of Flatbush and Church Aves.
October 1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(3)
The same, showing a closer view of the church from the opposite direction.
October 1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
